                                        1225,
                                        1956
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "4) Biological Control: Some beneficial microorganisms, such as certain strains of Trichoderma spp. or Bacillus spp., can antagonize plant pathogens and help suppress disease development. These biocontrol agents can be applied to the soil or foliage as a part of an integrated disease management approach [45], [50], [51], [54]. This requires regular scouting of ginger plants for signs of fungal diseases, such as leaf spots or rhizome rot, and take prompt action if symptoms are observed."
                                }
