                                        2554
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) is a powerful molecular biology technique used to amplify and detect DNA sequences associated with pathogens. For ginger diseases, PCR- based methods are used for precise and specific detection of various pathogens (viruses, bacteria, and fungi). Some of the PCR techniques are conventional PCR, real- time PCR (qPCR), reverse transcription PCR (RT- PCR), multiplex PCR, and nested PCR."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
